Novak Djokovic rallied from a set and a break down Tuesday to beat Alexandr Dolgopolov 6-7, 7-5, 6-0 in the fourth round of the Miami Open.

Dolgopolov led 4-1 in the second set before the world No 1 mounted a comeback to remain in contention for his fifth Key Biscayne title.

After the second set, Dolgopolov received treatment from a trainer, who bandaged the soles of both feet. 

