The Russian moved poorly after that and won only three of 27 points in the final set.

As Djokovic fell behind in the first set, he busted a racket in anger, drew jeers from the crowd and was cited for two code violations, which cost him a point penalty. 

However, he won a succession of long exchanges late in the second set that allowed him to even the match.

